[SN]TITLE[SN]
Queen's Park FC: Bring us the head of Harry the Hoopo

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scotland's oldest association football club has appealed for help in tracing the missing head of its mascot.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Queen's Park FC said Harry the Hoopo's head had recently been taken from the the JB McAlpine Pavilion, the Glasgow club's youth and community facility.
On Twitter, the club said: "To date we have received no ransom notes. We beseech you all to leave no stone unturned in the hunt for Harry's head."
Queen's Park appealed for anyone with information to get in touch.
The club plays at Hampden Park and is currently in Scottish League Two.
